name: Kevin whately
summary: British actor Kevin Whately, known for his roles in the television series "Inspector Morse" and "Vera," has been awarded an Order of the British Empire (OBE) in the 2025 New Year Honours. The honor recognizes his contributions to drama and television. Reports indicate that Whately has received this recognition for his diverse work, including his current role in the ongoing series "Vera." Despite his success, Whately has reportedly expressed a desire to move past his previous television appearances and focus on future projects.

name: Brentford vs Arsenal
summary: Arsenal emerged victorious in their Premier League matchup against Brentford, securing a 3-1 victory. The match witnessed a fierce battle between the two sides, with Brentford putting up a strong fightback after Arsenal took an early lead. However, Arsenal's resilience and determination ultimately proved too much for Brentford as they maintained their dominance in the match despite Brentford's spirited efforts. The result propelled Arsenal to second place in the Premier League standings, closing the gap on leaders Liverpool.

name: Elon Musk
summary: Elon Musk has been actively involved in politics and his recent actions have raised concerns. He has changed his Twitter handle to "Kekius Maximus," which has far-right connotations. Additionally, he has moved into a cottage on Donald Trump's Mar-a-Lago estate and penned an opinion piece supporting the far-right AfD party in Germany. These actions have led to accusations that he is trying to influence the upcoming German election. Musk has also been accused of censoring right-wing accounts on Twitter who disagree with him on immigration. Meanwhile, some top Democrats are warming up to his cost-cutting mission for the US government. In the UK, Musk has urged Britons to vote for Nigel Farage's party, Reform. Lastly, a New York Post report suggests that Trump supports immigration visas backed by Musk.

name: We Live in Time
summary: "We Live in Time" is a romantic drama film receiving mixed reviews. Critics praise the chemistry between Florence Pugh and Andrew Garfield, with Empire describing their performance as "a force." The Guardian also highlights their romance, while The Independent notes the film's ability to make the subject of cancer "remarkably cosy." Screen International discusses the challenges in bringing an original British romance to cinemas. GLAMOUR UK commends the film's portrayal of society's obsession with motherhood. However, inews finds the film contrived and not particularly clever, and The Irish Times questions its manipulation and effectiveness. My London provides information on the London locations featured in the film.

name: Vera
summary: The beloved detective drama "Vera" reaches its final chapter with the premiere of its fourteenth and final season on ITV. Fans eagerly await Brenda Blethyn's return as Detective Chief Inspector Vera Stanhope in the concluding episodes, which promise an emotional farewell after 14 years on screen. The season will feature familiar faces and new challenges, including a clash between Vera and her loyal colleague, Joe Ashworth, leaving viewers wondering about the fate of Kenny Lockhart. As the drama unfolds in its final episodes, audiences will be captivated by the gripping mysteries and the bittersweet conclusion of this long-running series.

name: James Corden
summary: James Corden has been discussing the reasoning behind certain plotlines in the recent Gavin and Stacey finale. He explained the "trick" twist in the Christmas Day special, while also sharing behind-the-scenes snaps from the filming. Corden and his co-star Ruth Jones spent the day together watching the finale. Despite rumors of a feud between Corden and Matthew Horne, the two remain friends. Corden believes that Smithy and Nessa's relationship was meant to end in the finale, while an extra from the show revealed details about Corden's on-set behavior. Sheridan Smith, who plays Nessa, reportedly canceled her autobiography after reuniting with Corden for the finale. Additionally, Corden emphasized that he and Jones must decline any BBC offers for a Gavin and Stacey continuation.
